        <mxCell id="PmzNDFpxscOfxV4MDq_8-16" value="&lt;h1&gt;The Midnight Library&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Author: Matt Haig&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Year: 2020&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Genre: Literary Fiction / Fantasy&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Summary: Nora Seed finds herself in a library between life and death, where each book represents a different version of her life. She must explore the roads not taken — different careers, relationships, and choices — to discover what makes life truly worth living.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recommendation: Based on your interest in stories about second chances and existential self-discovery, this novel&#39;s blend of philosophical depth and emotional warmth makes it a near-perfect match for your reading profile.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1640" y="920" width="360" height="320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="PmzNDFpxscOfxV4MDq_8-17" value="&lt;h1&gt;Never Let Me Go&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;Author: Kazuo Ishiguro&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Year: 2005&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Genre: Literary Fiction / Dystopian&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Summary: Told through the quiet reminiscences of Kathy H., this novel follows three friends raised at an idyllic English boarding school, slowly revealing the deeply unsettling truth about their existence and what society has planned for them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recommendation: You mentioned preferring books that linger with you long after the last page — Ishiguro&#39;s restrained prose and devastating emotional undercurrent make this exactly that kind of read.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1640" y="1240" width="360" height="320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="PmzNDFpxscOfxV4MDq_8-18" value="&lt;h1&gt;Piranesi&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Author: Susanna Clarke&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Year: 2020&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Genre: Fantasy / Mystery&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Summary: Piranesi lives in a vast, labyrinthine House filled with endless halls, statues, and tidal seas. As he pieces together the truth of his existence from his own journals, reality becomes increasingly strange and wondrous.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recommendation: Given your affinity for introspective narratives and a touch of the surreal, Piranesi&#39;s dreamlike mystery and compact, elegant structure should resonate strongly with you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1640" y="1560" width="360" height="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="PmzNDFpxscOfxV4MDq_8-19" value="&lt;h1&gt;A Gentleman in Moscow&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Author: Amor Towles&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Year: 2016&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Genre: Historical Fiction&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Summary: Count Alexander Rostov is sentenced to house arrest in a luxury Moscow hotel by a Bolshevik tribunal. Confined within its walls for decades, he finds purpose, love, and an entire world within what could have been a prison.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recommendation: Your conversation touched on themes of finding meaning in constraint and the richness of inner life — this book is practically written for that sensibility.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1640" y="1840" width="360" height="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="PmzNDFpxscOfxV4MDq_8-20" value="&lt;h1&gt;Flowers for Algernon&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Author: Daniel Keyes&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Year: 1966&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Genre: Science Fiction / Literary Fiction&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Summary: Charlie Gordon, a man with an intellectual disability, undergoes an experimental procedure that dramatically raises his IQ. Told through his own journal entries, the novel tracks his transformation — and its heartbreaking consequences.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recommendation: You expressed interest in books that challenge assumptions about intelligence and identity. Charlie&#39;s shifting perspective makes this one of the most emotionally honest explorations of what it means to be human in the genre.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1640" y="2120" width="360" height="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
